Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell: Pandora Tomorrow is a 2004 stealth game developed and published by 
Ubisoft Shanghai and Ubisoft Milan. The game is the sequel to Splinter Cell and the second game 
in the Splinter Cell series endorsed by writer Tom Clancy. It follows the covert activities of 
Sam Fisher, an agent working for a black-ops branch of the National Security Agency (NSA) called 
"Third Echelon". Michael Ironside returns to voice Sam Fisher, while Dennis Haysbert voices the 
character Irving Lambert, Fisher's boss, making this the only time he is not voiced by Don Jordan. 
Lalo Schifrin provides the theme music for the game. 